{"name":"Religion (Wis)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=13\">Religion</a>&nbsp;(Wis)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The secrets of deities, dogma, faith, and the realms of divine creatures both sublime and sinister are open to you. You also understand how magic works, though your training imparts a religious slant to that knowledge. Even if you&rsquo;re untrained in Religion, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><u style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=5&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.LZgjpWd0pL3vK9Q1]{Recall Knowledge (Religion)}</a></u></strong>&nbsp;about divine agents, the finer points of theology, obscure myths regarding a faith, and creatures of religious significance (like celestials, fiends, and undead), the Outer Sphere, and the Positive and Negative Energy Planes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Religion Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=1&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.d9gbpiQjChYDYA2L]{Decipher Writing}</a></strong>&nbsp;of a religious nature, including allegories, homilies, and proverbs.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.eReSHVEPCsdkSL4G]{Identify Magic}</strong>, particularly divine magic.</li>\n<li><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=4&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Q5iIYCFdqJFM31GW]{Learn a Spell}</a></strong>&nbsp;from the divine tradition.</li>\n</ul>","_id":"0jAYVVV4gJcpentE"}
{"name":"Thievery (Dex)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=17\">Thievery</a>&nbsp;(Dex)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You are trained in a particular set of skills favored by thieves and miscreants</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\"> Thievery Untrained Actions</span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.ijZ0DDFpMkWqaShd]{Palm an Object}<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.RDXXE7wMrSPCLv5k]{Steal}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\"> Thievery Trained Actions</span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.cYdz2grcOcRt4jk6]{Disable Device} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/TwoActions.png\" alt=\"Two Actions\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=70\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.2EE4aF4SZpYf0R6H]{Pick a Lock}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/TwoActions.png\" alt=\"Two Actions\" /></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"25ryBwQLGCOp6UJY"}
{"name":"Performance (Cha)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=12\">Performance</a>&nbsp;(Cha)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You are skilled at a form of performance, using your talents to impress a crowd or make a living.</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\"> Performance Trained Actions</span></span></strong></h2>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.QyzlsLrqM0EEwd7j]{Earn Income}</strong> by staging a performance.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Performance Untrained Actions</span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.EEDElIyin4z60PXx]{Perform}</strong></p>","_id":"75Txz21ldsZIFEpK"}
{"name":"Diplomacy (Cha)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=6\">Diplomacy</a>&nbsp;(Cha)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You influence others through negotiation and flattery.</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Diplomacy Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.plBGdZhqq5JBl1D8]{Gather Information}</strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.OX4fy22hQgUHDr0q]{Make an Impression}</strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.DCb62iCBrJXy0Ik6]{Request} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"AZQZNomhB90lRAdW"}
{"name":"Survival (Wis)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=16\">Survival</a>&nbsp;(Wis)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You are adept at living in the wilderness, foraging for food and building shelter, and with training you discover the secrets of tracking and hiding your trail. Even if you’re untrained, you can still use Survival to Subsist.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.49y9Ec4bDii8pcD3]{Subsist}</strong> in the wild by foraging for food and building shelter.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Survival Untrained Actions</span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.fJImDBQfqfjKJOhk]{Sense Direction}</strong></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Survival Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.SB7cMECVtE06kByk]{Cover Tracks}</strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.EA5vuSgJfiHH7plD]{Track}</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"FxpE1kVOXB377CLb"}
{"name":"Acrobatics (Dex)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=1\">Acrobatics</a>&nbsp;(Dex)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Acrobatics measures your ability to perform tasks requiring coordination and grace. When you use the @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.SkZAQRkLLkmBQNB9]{Escape} basic action, you can use your Acrobatics modifier instead of your unarmed attack modifier.</span></span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Acrobatics Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.M76ycLAqHoAgbcej]{Balance}</span></span><img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.21WIfSu7Xd7uKqV8]{Tumble Through}</span></span></strong></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Trained Actions</span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Qf1ylAbdVi1rkc8M]{Maneuver in Flight}</span></span><img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.kMcV8e5EZUxa6evt]{Squeeze}</span></span></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"LsiJCe2vBpAcPRkv"}
{"name":"Intimidation (Cha)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=7\">Intimidation</a>&nbsp;(Cha)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You bend others to your will using threats.</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Intimidation Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=52\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.tHCqgwjtQtzNqVvd]{Coerce}</a></p>\n<p><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=53\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.2u915NdUyQan6uKF]{Demoralize}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"MjCvzmAMm976yuZH"}
{"name":"Lore (Int)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=8\">Lore</a>&nbsp;(Int)</h1>\n<div class=\"sidebar\" style=\"margin: 0.5em; float: right; width: 300px; border: thin solid black; background-color: #d3d3d3; padding: 0.5em; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">\n<h2 style=\"margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; font-size: 1.3em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">Common Lore Subcategories</h2>\nYou can learn any Lore skill your GM gives you permission to take. The following list covers a wide variety of common Lore topics appropriate for most campaigns. Backgrounds often grant you a Lore from this list.\n<ul>\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">Academia Lore</li>\n<li>Accounting Lore</li>\n<li>Architecture Lore</li>\n<li>Art Lore</li>\n<li>Circus Lore</li>\n<li>Engineering Lore</li>\n<li>Farming Lore</li>\n<li>Fishing Lore</li>\n<li>Fortune-Telling Lore</li>\n<li>Games Lore</li>\n<li>Genealogy Lore</li>\n<li>Gladiatorial Lore</li>\n<li>Guild Lore</li>\n<li>Heraldry Lore</li>\n<li>Herbalism Lore</li>\n<li>Hunting Lore</li>\n<li>Labor Lore</li>\n<li>Legal Lore</li>\n<li>Library Lore</li>\n<li>Lore about a specific deity <strong>(@Compendium[pf2e.crb-srd.d56paSkcwvll2OhR]{Abadar}</strong> Lore, <strong>@Compendium[pf2e.crb-srd.eErEiVmBqltYXFJ6]{Iomedae}</strong>&nbsp;Lore, etc.)</li>\n<li>Lore about a specific creature or narrow category of creatures (Demon Lore, Owlbear Lore, Vampire Lore, etc.)</li>\n<li>Lore of a specific plane other than the Material Plane, or the plane in which the game is set if not the Material Plane (Abyss Lore, Astral Plane Lore, Heaven Lore, etc.)</li>\n<li>Lore about a specific settlement (Absalom Lore, Magnimar Lore, etc.)</li>\n<li>Lore about a specific terrain (Mountain Lore, River Lore, etc.)</li>\n<li>Lore of a type of food or drink (Alcohol Lore, Baking Lore, Butchering Lore, Cooking Lore, Tea Lore, etc.)</li>\n<li>Mercantile Lore</li>\n<li>Midwifery Lore</li>\n<li>Milling Lore</li>\n<li>Mining Lore</li>\n<li>Sailing Lore</li>\n<li>Scouting Lore</li>\n<li>Scribing Lore</li>\n<li>Stabling Lore</li>\n<li>Tanning Lore</li>\n<li>Theater Lore</li>\n<li>Underworld Lore</li>\n<li>Warfare Lore</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.1OagaWtBpVXExToo]{Recall Knowledge (Lore)}</strong> about the subject of your Lore skill’s subcategory.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Lore Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.QyzlsLrqM0EEwd7j]{Earn Income}</strong> by using your knowledge to practice a trade.</li>\n</ul>","_id":"Nuy5AH3q6RXXbXok"}
{"name":"Medicine (Wis)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=9\">Medicine</a>&nbsp;(Wis)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You can patch up wounds and help people recover from diseases and poisons. Even if you&rsquo;re untrained in Medicine, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Medicine Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=54\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.MHLuKy4nQO2Z4Am1]{Administer First Aid}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/TwoActions.png\" alt=\"Two Actions\" /></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Medicine Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.TC7OcDa7JlWbqMaN]{Treat Disease}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.KjoCEEmPGTeFE4hh]{Treat Poison} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.1kGNdIIhuglAjIp9]{Treat Wounds}</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"P3IcwePWZfnTld46"}
{"name":"Occultism (Int)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=11\">Occultism</a>&nbsp;(Int)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You know a great deal about ancient philosophies, esoteric lore, obscure mysticism, and supernatural creatures. Even if you&rsquo;re untrained in Occultism, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=5&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.B2BpIZFHoF9Kjzpx]{Recall Knowledge (Occultism)}</a></strong>&nbsp;about ancient mysteries; obscure philosophies; creatures of occult significance (like aberrations, spirits, and oozes); and the Positive Energy, Negative Energy, Shadow, Astral, and Ethereal Planes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Occultism Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.d9gbpiQjChYDYA2L]{Decipher Writing} </strong>on occult topics, including complex metaphysical systems, syncretic principles, weird philosophies, and incoherent ramblings.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.eReSHVEPCsdkSL4G]{Identify Magic}</strong>, particularly occult magic.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Q5iIYCFdqJFM31GW]{Learn a Spell}</strong>&nbsp;from the occult tradition.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"ZLS8j0n7BKpsQqOy"}
{"name":"Athletics (Str)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=3\">Athletics</a>&nbsp;(Str)</h1>\n<div class=\"sidebar\" style=\"margin: 0.5em; float: right; width: 300px; border: thin solid black; background-color: #d3d3d3; padding: 0.5em; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">\n<h2 style=\"margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; font-size: 15px; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">Falling</h2>\nWhen you fall more than 5 feet, you take falling damage when you land, which is bludgeoning damage equal to half the distance you fell. If you take any damage from a fall, you’re knocked prone when you land.<br><br>If you fall into water, snow, or another soft substance, calculate the damage from the fall as though your fall were 20 feet shorter. The reduction can’t be greater than the depth of the water (so when falling into water that is only 10 feet deep, you treat the fall as 10 feet shorter). You can Grab an Edge as a reaction (page 472) to reduce or eliminate the damage from some falls. More detailed rules for falling damage appear on page 463.</div>\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Athletics allows you to perform deeds of physical prowess. When you use the&nbsp;</span><a style=\"color: inherit; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=79\">Escape</a><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"> basic action, you can use your Athletics modifier instead of your unarmed attack modifier.</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Athletics Untrained Actions</span></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.pprgrYQ1QnIDGZiy]{Climb}&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=34\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.SjmKHgI7a5Z9JzBx]{Force Open}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.PMbdMWc2QroouFGD]{Grapple} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.2HJ4yuEFY1Cast4h]{High Jump} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/TwoActions.png\" alt=\"Two Actions\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.JUvAvruz7yRQXfz2]{Long Jump} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/TwoActions.png\" alt=\"Two Actions\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.7blmbDrQFNfdT731]{Shove}<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.c8TGiZ48ygoSPofx]{Swim} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.ge56Lu1xXVFYUnLP]{Trip} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></strong></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Athletics Trained Actions</span></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Dt6B1slsBy8ipJu9]{Disarm</strong>} <img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"n0R7CBG4Qi4dIfOC"}
{"name":"Deception (Cha)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=5\">Deception</a>&nbsp;(Cha)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You can trick and mislead others using disguises, lies, and other forms of subterfuge.</span></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Deception Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=45\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.GkmbTGfg8KcgynOA]{Create a Diversion}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.AJstokjdG6iDjVjE]{Impersonate}</strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.ewwCglB7XOPLUz72]{Lie}</strong></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Deception Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=48\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.QNAVeNKtHA0EUw4X]{Feint}</a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"nHeLjd6pLbYP0xVt"}
{"name":"Crafting (Int)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; margin-left: -2px; padding: 4px 9px; background-color: #522e2c; color: #cbc18f; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=4\">Crafting</a>&nbsp;(Int)</h1>\n<div class=\"sidebar\" style=\"margin: 0.5em; float: right; width: 300px; border: thin solid black; background-color: #d3d3d3; padding: 0.5em; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">\n<h2 style=\"margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; font-size: 1.3em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">Crafting Example</h2>\nEzren is a 5th-level wizard and an expert in Crafting. He has a Crafting modifier of +13 and the <strong>@Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.xWY5omyIcILNR7y1]{Magical Crafting}</strong> feat. With 2 weeks of downtime ahead of him, he decides to craft a <strong>@Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.DxCuJKynlnMQZHgp]{Striking Ruin}</strong>, a 4th-level item. The GM secretly chooses a DC of 19.<br><br>The item has a Price of 65 gp, so Ezren prepares 32 gp, 5 sp worth of raw materials. He has another 32 gp, 5 sp worth of raw materials on hand. After spending 4 days building and incanting spells, he rolls a 12 on his Crafting check, for a result of 25. That’s a success! At this point, Ezren can spend the additional 32 gp, 5 sp worth of materials to complete the item immediately for 65 gp. However, Ezren has 10 more days on his hands, so he decides to spend additional time to complete the item. Because he’s a 5th-level character and an expert at Crafting, he reduces the amount he has to pay by 1 gp for each day spent. After spending 10 days working, he reduces the cost to complete the item from 65 gp to 55 gp. He spends the remaining portion of its Price in materials, completes the&nbsp;<em>striking rune</em>, and goes out on his next adventure. (He could have stayed home to keep working on the&nbsp;<em>striking rune</em>, eventually reducing the item’s total Price to just the half he paid up front, but adventuring is far more lucrative!)<br><br>If Ezren’s Crafting check result were a 29 or higher, he’d have gotten a critical success. In that case, he’d reduce the remaining amount by 2 gp per day, lowering the amount needed to complete the item after 10 additional days of work to 45 gp.</div>\n</div>\n<p>You can use this skill to create, understand, and repair items. Even if you’re untrained, you can Recall Knowledge</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.B0Eu3EfwIa9kyDEA]{Recall Knowledge (Crafting)}</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: bold;\">Crafting Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.bT3skovyLUtP22ME]{Repair}</strong></p>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: bold;\"> Crafting Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.QyzlsLrqM0EEwd7j]{Earn Income}</strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.rmwa3OyhTZ2i2AHl]{Craft}</strong></p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Q4kdWVOf2ztIBFg1]{Identify Alchemy}</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"qHvg5lzUJv8uJaAz"}
{"name":"Stealth (Dex)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=15\">Stealth</a>&nbsp;(Dex)</h1>\n<p>You are skilled at avoiding detection, allowing you to slip past foes, hide, or conceal an item.</p>\n<h2>Stealth Untrained Actions</h2>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.qVNVSmsgpKFGk9hV]{Conceal an Object}&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 20px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.XMcnh4cSI32tljXa]{Hide}&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 20px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.VMozDqMMuK5kpoX4]{Sneak}<img style=\"height: 20px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; font-size: 1.3em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">Being Stealthy</h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">If you want to sneak around when there are creatures that can see you, you can use a combination of Hide and Sneak to do so.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">First, Hide behind something (either by taking advantage of cover or having the concealed condition due to fog, a spell, or a similar effect). A successful Stealth check makes you hidden, though the creatures still know roughly where you are.</li>\n<li>Second, now that you&rsquo;re hidden, you can Sneak. That means you can move at half your Speed and attempt another Stealth check. If it&rsquo;s successful, you&rsquo;re now undetected. That means the creatures don&rsquo;t know which square you&rsquo;re in anymore.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">If you were approaching creatures that didn&rsquo;t know you were there, you could begin Sneaking right away, since they didn&rsquo;t know your location to start with. Some actions can cause you to become observed again, but they&rsquo;re mostly what you&rsquo;d expect: standing out in the open, attacking someone, making a bunch of noise, and so forth. If you Strike someone after successfully Hiding or Sneaking, though, they&rsquo;re flat-footed to that Strike.<br /></span><br /><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Creatures can try to find you using the Seek action, described on page 471.</span><br style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; background-color: #d3d3d3;\" /><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><br />Three conditions explain the states of detection. Remember that these conditions are relative to each creature&mdash;you can be observed by one creature while hidden to another and undetected by a third.</span></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\" style=\"font-size: 1.1em; margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">Observed</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You&rsquo;re in the creature&rsquo;s clear view.</span></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\" style=\"font-size: 1.1em; margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">Hidden</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The creature knows your location but can&rsquo;t see you.</span></p>\n<h3 class=\"framing\" style=\"font-size: 1.1em; margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">Undetected</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The creature doesn&rsquo;t know your location.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"qvSO3KAfzIPGX7mS"}
{"_id":"rFDUA23lJFFAlKIQ","name":"Arcana (Int)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=2\">Arcana</a>&nbsp;(Int)</h1>\n<p>Measures how much you know about arcane magic and creatures. Even if you&rsquo;re untrained, you can Recall Knowledge.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.KygTSeDvsFoSO6HW]{Recall Knowledge (Arcana)}</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Arcana Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.d9gbpiQjChYDYA2L]{Decipher Writing} </strong>about arcane theory.<u style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"></u></li>\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: Century Gothic, CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.eReSHVEPCsdkSL4G]{Identify Magic}, </strong>particularly arcane magic.</span></span></li>\n<li style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Q5iIYCFdqJFM31GW]{Learn a Spell}</strong>&nbsp;from the arcane tradition.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Arcana Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.OizxuPb44g3eHPFh]{Borrow an Arcane Spell}</strong></p>\n<hr style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\" />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}
{"name":"Society (Int)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=14\">Society</a>&nbsp;(Int)</h1>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You understand the people and systems that make civilization run, and you know the historical events that make societies what they are today. Further, you can use that knowledge to navigate the complex physical, societal, and economic workings of settlements. Even if you&rsquo;re untrained in Society, you can use it for the following general skill actions.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=5&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.KUfLlXDWTcAWhl8l]{Recall Knowledge (Society)}</a></strong>&nbsp;about local history, important personalities, legal institutions, societal structure, and humanoid cultures. The GM might allow Society to apply to other creatures that are major elements of society in your region, such as the draconic nobility in a kingdom of humans ruled by dragons.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.49y9Ec4bDii8pcD3]{Subsist}</strong> in a settlement by finding shelter, scrounging, or begging for food.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"title\" style=\"margin: 1em 0em 10px -2px; font-size: 1.3em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; color: #1b1007; padding: 4px 9px; line-height: 16px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Society Trained Actions</h2>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.d9gbpiQjChYDYA2L]{Decipher Writing}</strong> that&rsquo;s a coded message, text written in an incomplete or archaic form, or in some cases, text in a language you don&rsquo;t know.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"> Society Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.ftG89SjTSa9DYDOD]{Create Forgery}</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"vETxD8piovjGwpjd"}
{"name":"Nature (Wis)","permission":{"default":0,"EGIKXMb8Ryl5TZeb":3},"flags":{},"content":"<h1 class=\"title\" style=\"font-size: 1.75em; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #522e2c; margin-left: -2px; color: #cbc18f; padding: 4px 9px; min-height: 26px; border-radius: 3px; vertical-align: middle; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=10\">Nature</a>&nbsp;(Wis)</h1>\n<div class=\"sidebar\" style=\"margin: 0.5em; float: right; width: 300px; border: thin solid black; background-color: #d3d3d3; padding: 0.5em; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">\n<h2 style=\"margin-right: 0em; margin-bottom: 0em; margin-left: 0em; font-size: 1.3em; text-indent: 0em; font-weight: bold; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">Commanded Animals</h2>\nIssuing commands to an animal doesn’t always go smoothly. An animal is an independent creature with limited intelligence. Most animals understand only the simplest instructions, so you might be able to instruct your animal to move to a certain square but not dictate a specific path to get there, or command it to attack a certain creature but not to make its attack nonlethal. The GM decides the specifics of the action your animal uses.<br><br>The animal does what you commanded as soon as it can, usually as its first action on its next turn. If you successfully commanded it multiple times, it does what you said in order. It forgets all commands beyond what it can accomplish on its turn. If multiple people command the same animal, the GM determines how the animal reacts. The GM might also make the DC higher if someone has already tried to Command the Animal that round.</div>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">You know a great deal about the natural world, and you command and train animals and magical beasts. Even if you’re untrained in Nature, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.</span></p>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.eT1jXYvz2YH70Ovp]{Recall Knowledge (Nature)}</strong>about fauna, flora, geography, weather, the environment, creatures of natural origin (like animals, beasts, fey, and plants), the First World, the Material Plane, and the Elemental Planes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Nature Trained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<ul style=\"color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><u style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=3&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.eReSHVEPCsdkSL4G]{Identify Magic}</a></u></strong>, particularly primal magic.</li>\n<li><strong style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><u style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Skills.aspx?ID=4&amp;General=true\">@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Q5iIYCFdqJFM31GW]{Learn a Spell}</a></u></strong>&nbsp;from the primal tradition.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #0f0f0f; font-family: 'Century Gothic', CenturyGothic, AppleGothic, sans-serif;\">Nature Untrained Actions</span></strong></h2>\n<p><a style=\"margin-top: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; color: inherit;\" href=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Actions.aspx?ID=58\"><strong>@Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.q9nbyIF0PEBqMtYe]{Command an Animal}</strong></a>&nbsp;<img style=\"height: 15px;\" src=\"https://2e.aonprd.com/Images/Actions/OneAction.png\" alt=\"Single Action\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","_id":"xEx4S9eticDFR8uT"}
